# Premium Portfolio Website - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Building a premium authority website for a web developer. Goal: Position as high-end expert and convert visitors into serious, higher-value client inquiries.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS v4
- Framer Motion
- React Hook Form + Zod
- Resend (email)

## Code Style & Standards

### TypeScript
- Always use TypeScript, never `any` types
- Define interfaces for all props and data structures
- Use type inference where obvious
- Export types alongside components

### Component Structure
```typescript
// Preferred pattern
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  description?: string;
}

export function Component({ title, description }: ComponentProps) {
  return (
    <div>
      {/* component content */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `Hero.tsx`, `ProjectCard.tsx`)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `formatDate.ts`, `emailService.ts`)
- Data files: camelCase (e.g., `projects.ts`, `services.ts`)
- Pages: kebab-case for routes (e.g., `request-quote/page.tsx`)

### Import Order
1. React/Next.js imports
2. Third-party libraries
3. Local components
4. Local utilities/data
5. Types
6. Styles (if applicable)

```typescript
import { useState } from 'react';
import Link from 'next/link';
import { motion } from 'framer-motion';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';
import { formatDate } from '@/lib/utils';
import type { Project } from '@/types';
```

## Design System Rules

### Colors
- Primary: Navy `#1a202c`
- Accent: Gold `#d4af37`
- Neutrals: Tailwind gray scale
- Never use arbitrary hex values, use Tailwind classes

### Typography
- Headings: `font-serif` (Playfair Display)
- Body: `font-sans` (Inter)
- Hierarchy:
  - h1: `text-4xl md:text-6xl`
  - h2: `text-3xl md:text-5xl`
  - h3: `text-2xl md:text-4xl`
  - body: `text-base md:text-lg`

### Spacing
- Section padding: `py-16 md:py-24`
- Container max-width: `max-w-7xl`
- Card padding: `p-6 md:p-8`
- Use Tailwind spacing scale, no arbitrary values

## Tailwind CSS v4 Configuration

### Critical: New Syntax
Tailwind v4 uses a completely different setup than v3:

**globals.css (REQUIRED):**
```css
@import "tailwindcss";
```

Do NOT use old v3 syntax:
```css
/* ❌ WRONG - Don't use this */
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;
```

**PostCSS Configuration:**
```javascript
// postcss.config.mjs
export default {
  plugins: {
    '@tailwindcss/postcss': {},
    autoprefixer: {},
  },
};
```

**Installation:**
```bash
npm install -D tailwindcss@next @tailwindcss/postcss autoprefixer
```

### Custom Theme (Optional)
If you need custom colors/fonts, create `tailwind.config.ts`:
```typescript
import type { Config } from 'tailwindcss';

const config: Config = {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        primary: '#1a202c',
        accent: '#d4af37',
      },
      fontFamily: {
        sans: ['var(--font-inter)'],
        serif: ['var(--font-playfair)'],
      },
    },
  },
};

export default config;
```

### Animations
- Use Framer Motion for all animations
- Duration: 0.3-0.5s
- Easing: `ease-out` or `ease-in-out`
- Subtle only - no flashy effects
- Fade in on scroll with `useInView` hook

```typescript
// Standard fade-in pattern
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.5 }}
>
  {content}
</motion.div>
```

## Component Guidelines

### Button Component
- Always use the shared `Button` component
- Variants: `primary`, `secondary`, `ghost`
- Sizes: `sm`, `md`, `lg`
- Never style buttons inline

### Image Optimization
- Always use Next.js `Image` component
- Provide `alt` text for accessibility
- Use `priority` for above-fold images
- Set explicit width/height or use `fill` prop

### Links
- Internal links: Use Next.js `Link` component
- External links: Add `rel="noopener noreferrer"`
- CTAs should always link to `/quote`

### Forms
- Use React Hook Form + Zod validation
- Show validation errors inline
- Disable submit button during submission
- Show success/error messages
- Clear form after successful submission

## Data Management

### Project Data Structure
```typescript
interface Project {
  slug: string;
  title: string;
  tagline: string;
  problem: string;
  solution: string;
  results: string[];
  technologies: string[];
  thumbnail: string;
  images: string[];
  featured: boolean;
}
```

### Data Files Location
- All data in `data/` directory
- Export as typed arrays
- No hardcoded content in components
- Use descriptive variable names

## Performance Rules

### Images
- Optimize all images before adding to `public/`
- Target: <500KB per image
- Use WebP format when possible
- Lazy load below-fold images

### Bundle Size
- Import only what you need from libraries
- Use dynamic imports for heavy components
- Monitor bundle size with `next build`

### Loading States
- Show skeleton loaders for async content
- Disable forms during submission
- Use `loading.tsx` for route transitions

## Accessibility

### Required Standards
- All images have descriptive `alt` text
- Color contrast ratio: minimum 4.5:1
- Keyboard navigation works throughout
- Focus states visible on all interactive elements
- Form labels properly associated with inputs

### Semantic HTML
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)
- Use `<nav>` for navigation
- Use `<main>` for main content
- Use `<section>` for content sections
- Use `<article>` for blog posts/case studies

## SEO Requirements

### Metadata
- Every page must have unique title and description
- Title format: "[Page Name] | [Developer Name]"
- Description: 150-160 characters
- Include Open Graph tags for social sharing

### Structure
- One h1 per page
- Logical heading hierarchy
- Descriptive URLs (e.g., `/portfolio/ecommerce-redesign`)
- Internal linking between related pages

## Premium Design Principles

### White Space
- Generous padding and margins
- Let content breathe
- Never cram elements together
- Mobile: minimum 1rem padding on edges

### Visual Hierarchy
- Clear distinction between primary/secondary content
- Use size, weight, and color to guide eye
- Important CTAs should stand out

### Consistency
- Reuse components, don't recreate
- Maintain consistent spacing patterns
- Use design system tokens

### Polish
- Smooth transitions on all interactive elements
- Hover states on clickable elements
- Loading states for async operations
- Error states that guide recovery

## Content Guidelines

### Tone
- Professional but approachable
- Confident, not arrogant
- Focus on outcomes, not technical details
- Business language, not developer jargon

### Copy Rules
- No Lorem Ipsum in production
- Active voice over passive
- Short sentences and paragraphs
- Scannable content with clear headings

### CTAs
- Action-oriented ("Request a Quote", "View Portfolio")
- Every page should have a clear next step
- Primary CTA: Get in touch / Request quote
- Make CTAs stand out visually

## API Routes

### Structure
```typescript
// app/api/[endpoint]/route.ts
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server';

export async function POST(request: Request) {
  try {
    // Validate input with Zod
    // Process request
    // Return success response
    return NextResponse.json({ success: true });
  } catch (error) {
    // Log error
    // Return error response
    return NextResponse.json(
      { error: 'Message' },
      { status: 500 }
    );
  }
}
```

### Security
- Validate all inputs
- Rate limit if needed
- Sanitize user data
- Never expose API keys
- Use environment variables

