## Git Commit Messages

Format: `type: description`

Types:
- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `style`: UI/styling changes
- `refactor`: Code restructuring
- `docs`: Documentation
- `chore`: Maintenance tasks

Examples:
- `feat: add hero section to homepage`
- `fix: mobile menu not closing on link click`
- `style: adjust button hover states`

## Deployment (Vercel)

### Pre-deployment
1. Run `npm run build` locally
2. Fix any build errors
3. Test production build with `npm run start`
4. Verify environment variables are set

### Post-deployment
1. Test all pages on live site
2. Test form submissions
3. Check performance (Lighthouse)
4. Verify SSL certificate
5. Test on multiple devices

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

❌ Don't:
- Use inline styles
- Hardcode content in components
- Use `any` type in TypeScript
- Ignore TypeScript errors
- Skip image optimization
- Forget alt text on images
- Use absolute positioning excessively
- Create one-off components (reuse!)
- Skip mobile testing
- Commit API keys

✅ Do:
- Use Tailwind utility classes
- Store content in data files
- Use proper TypeScript types
- Fix all TS errors before committing
- Optimize all images
- Provide descriptive alt text
- Use flexbox/grid for layouts
- Create reusable components
- Test on mobile first
- Use environment variables

## Questions to Ask Before Coding

1. Does this component already exist?
2. Can this be reused elsewhere?
3. Is this the simplest solution?
4. Have I typed this properly?
5. Will this work on mobile?
6. Is this accessible?
7. Does this match the design system?
8. Will this perform well?

